    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    Vita tells Leonard about a rumor the heard regarging a
                    change in the management of the Press. She asks if some
                    of her book can be re-printed. She asks if the rumor is true.
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <persName>
                              <choice>
                              <orig>Leonard</orig><reg>Leonard Woolf</reg>
                              </choice>
                            </persName>
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        My dear <choice>
                        <orig>Leonard</orig>
                        <reg>Leonard Woolf</reg>
                        </choice>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I have just received the enclosed letter <lb/>
                    which speaks for itself. I don't know if there <lb/>
                    is any truth in the rumor that the <orgName> Press </orgName>
                    <note><p> The Hogarth Press </p></note> is <lb/>
                    changing hands, although I do not know that John <lb/>
                    Lehmann has left it. I should of course be glad <lb/>
                    if certain of my books could be reprintes, namely <lb/>
                    Pepita, <choice> <orig> the two books about Persia </orig>
                    <reg> <title> Twelve Days: an account of a journey across
                    the Bakhtiari Mountains of South-western Persia </title>
                    <title> Passenger to Teheran </title> </reg> </choice>,
                    <title> The Edwardians </title> <lb/>
                    and <title> All Passion Spent </title>.
                    Could you let me know <lb/>
                    what the position is and if there is no truth <lb/>
                    in the story that you are giving up the Press, <lb/>
                    please forgive me for having written. <lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                  <dateline>
                      <placeName>
                        Sissinghurst Castle, Kent
                      </placeName>
                      <date when="1946-04-04">
                          4th April 1946
                      </date>
                  </dateline>
                  <address>
                      <addrLine>
                          <persName> Vita Sakville-West </persName>
                      </addrLine>
                      <addrLine>
                          Sissinghurst Castle, Kent
                      </addrLine>
                  </address>
                    <salute>
                        Yours ever,
                    </salute>
                    <signed> Vita </signed>
                    <address>
                      <addrLine> {Sissinghurst Castle, Kent} </addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
